        <title locale="en_US">A new species of &lt;i&gt;Pseudococcus &lt;/i&gt;(Hemiptera: Pseudococcidae) belonging to the “&lt;i&gt;Pseudococcus maritimus&lt;/i&gt;” complex from Chile: molecular and morphological description</title>
        <abstract locale="en_US">A new species of mealybug from Chile, &lt;i&gt;Pseudococcus&lt;/i&gt; &lt;i&gt;meridionalis&lt;/i&gt; Prado &lt;b&gt;sp.&lt;/b&gt; &lt;b&gt;n.,&lt;/b&gt; is described and illustrated based on the morphological and molecular characterization of adult females. This species belongs to the “Pseudococcus &lt;i&gt;maritimus”&lt;/i&gt; complex and displays a wide host plant range, including Japanese pear, persimmon, pomegranate, pear and grape.</abstract>
